18 Preamble
19 WHEREAS, The year 2017 marked 100 years since the Bolshevik Revolution in
20 Russia, which resulted in the world’s first communist regime under Vladimir Lenin and led
21 to decades of oppression and violence under communist regimes throughout the world; and
22 WHEREAS, Based on the philosophy of Karl Marx, communism has proven
23 incompatible with the ideals of liberty, prosperity, and dignity of human life and has given
24 rise to such infamous totalitarian dictators as Joseph Stalin, Mao Zedong, Ho Chi Minh,
25 Pol Pot, Nicolae Ceausescu, the Castro brothers, and the Kim dynasty; and
